    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1972-07-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1972-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <head>322. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d322fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1"
                            >Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Files, Box 138, <persName corresp="#p_KHA1"
                            >Kissinger</persName> Office Files, <persName corresp="#p_KHA1"
                            >Kissinger</persName> Country Files, Middle East, Kurdish Problem Vol.
                        I, June ′72–Oct. ′73. Secret; Sensitive; Exclusively Eyes Only. <persName
                            corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> approved the idea that Rob Roy
                        Ratliffe would handle the matter henceforth, adding a note that “he should
                        see me.” This document was Tab B to a July 31 memorandum from Tom Latimer of
                        the National Security Council Staff to <persName corresp="#p_HBMJ1"
                            >Haig</persName>. (Ibid.)</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d322fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName> advised the 40 Committee
                        principles that the President had authorized funds and supplies to assist
                            <persName>Barzani</persName>’s resistance movement.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                        ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                        calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1972-07-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                        notBefore="1972-07-28T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <pb facs="d322-01" n="1" xml:id="d322-01"/>
                <list>
                    <head>MEMORANDUM FOR:</head>
                    <item>The Under Secretary of State for Political Affairs</item>
                    <item>The Deputy Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Chairman, Joint Chiefs of Staff</item>
                    <item>The Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                </list>
                <p>In order to assist Mulla Mustafa Barzani and the Iraqi Kurds in their resistance
                    against the Bathi Iraqi regime, the President has directed that the following
                    actions be taken: <list>
                        <item>—The U.S. will provide the sum of [<hi rend="italic">text not
                                declassified</hi>] over one year, or a total of $3 million. Director
                                <persName corresp="#p_HRM1">Helms</persName> will furnish this
                            assistance through his channels.</item>
                        <item>—The U.S. will also supply roughly $2 million in supplies (exclusive
                            of transportation costs). The ordnance is to be delivered via <gloss
                                target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> channels.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
